extends layout

block content
  header(id='header-index')
    img(src='/images/header.png',width='100%')
  article(data-role='content')
    p.
      <b>PourMe</b> helps you (one day, anyway!) find local beers near you! If you're enjoying a drink right now, <a href="/add">add your drink</a> and help others know where they can enjoy what you're drinking.

    a(href='/add',data-role='button',data-icon='plus',data-theme='b') Add your drink

    p.
      It begins in Albuquerque and the <a href="http://albuquerque.startupweekend.org/">Albuquerque Startup Weekend!</a>

    h3 Find a brew
    form(method='post',action = '/search',data-ajax="false")
        input(type='search', name='beerQuery',placeholder="What's the name of your beer?")
        input(type='submit',value='Find Brew',data-icon='search')

    If you can't find anything (that's OK; the search engine isn't very good), check the <a href="/list">list of everything we have</a>.

    h3 Connect with us!
    p.
      At the 2013 Albuquerque Startup Weekend, a team of five people created <a href="http://pourme.co/">PourMe.co</a>, a startup company promoting a mobile app that links local users to local beers near them.  The project includes Samat Jain, Antonio Arredondo, and Zetdi Runyan from Las Cruces; Jose Trigueros, from San Luis, Arizona; and Morgan R. Nelson from Albuquerque.  Together the team brings together brings 45 years experience in three cutting-edge technologies, marketing, business development, and project management.

